summary: The document is a CIA record released under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992, detailing an interview with Charlotte Z. Bustos-Videla, an Operations Officer, conducted on 10 January 1973. The interview was part of an investigation into acquaintances or contacts of a person referred to as 'Agee'. Mrs. Bustos-Videla could not provide additional information about Agee but suggested contacting Dorothy Hennick for further inquiries.
key_findings: The document is part of the records released under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992.
Charlotte Z. Bustos-Videla was interviewed regarding her acquaintance with 'Agee' but could not provide additional information.
The interview suggests following up with Dorothy Hennick for more information on 'Agee's contacts.
keywords: President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992
